Janet Megamix 04 is a Megamix produced by veteran DJ Chris Cox, released in December 11, 2003 to promote Jackson&#039;s album "Damita Jo".

The single is a megamix by Chris Cox, containing 15 of Jackson&#039;s singles, and released ahead of the first commercial single "Just a Little While" from the 2004 album "Damita Jo". During the production of the remix, Cox&#039;s studio in California was ravaged by wildfire, and the DJ had to evacuate it midway through the project. The single entered the Billboard Hot Dance Club Play at number 34 and charted for 11 weeks, peaking at number 3.

The full megamix includes (in order of appearance) "That&#039;s The Way Love Goes", "Son of a Gun (I Betcha Think This Song Is About You)", "If", "Got &#039;Til It&#039;s Gone", "Doesn&#039;t Really Matter", "Go Deep", "You Want This", "All For You", "I Get Lonely", "Someone to Call My Lover", "Throb", "Again", "Together Again".

The single was released in several international territories but was not eligible for mainstream charts as it was not release commercially. The only version available on a commercial format is "Janet Megamix 04" (Chris Cox Club Mix) which appears as a b-side on the UK CD Single of "Just a Little While".

A music video for "Janet Megamix 04" was produced using the Radio Edit version of the track and features a montage of footage from Jackson&#039;s other videos used in the single. The video has never been released commercially.
